1
00:00:58,547 --> 00:01:02,971
[Episode 13: Between Cool and Passion]

2
00:01:05,588 --> 00:01:06,625
So?

3
00:01:06,625 --> 00:01:07,924
What happened?

4
00:01:07,924 --> 00:01:10,549
So I asked...

5
00:01:10,549 --> 00:01:13,942
"Then why was the dragon there
in the first place?"

6
00:01:13,942 --> 00:01:15,133
"I mean, it's not like..."

7
00:01:15,133 --> 00:01:18,799
"a dragon just flies around for no reason,
right?"

8
00:01:18,799 --> 00:01:21,941
They said,
"The sky looked empty, so I just added one."

9
00:01:21,941 --> 00:01:23,174
Can you believe that?

10
00:01:23,174 --> 00:01:25,733
They're always like that. Seriously.

11
00:01:25,733 --> 00:01:27,383
And when they get called out, they're like,
"What did I do wrong?"

12
00:01:27,383 --> 00:01:29,758
<i>For someone in low-power mode,</i>

13
00:01:29,758 --> 00:01:32,158
<i>this is how you survive a team dinner.</i>

14
00:01:36,091 --> 00:01:39,950
<i>You stop thinking.</i>

15
00:01:40,633 --> 00:01:43,086
Let's just rest.

16
00:01:46,049 --> 00:01:48,049
<i>Trying to conserve energy,</i>

17
00:01:48,049 --> 00:01:50,562
<i>the village stays dim,</i>

18
00:01:51,591 --> 00:01:54,557
<i>and kind of lifeless.</i>

19
00:01:57,217 --> 00:01:59,284
It's cold.

20
00:02:01,091 --> 00:02:04,131
What do you think, PD Shin?

21
00:02:05,508 --> 00:02:07,750
Not sure.

22
00:02:07,750 --> 00:02:08,811
That's it?

23
00:02:08,811 --> 00:02:12,055
Nothing really comes to mind.

24
00:02:12,055 --> 00:02:15,417
- Oh my, that's cold.
- So cold.

25
00:02:15,417 --> 00:02:18,884
<i>People call that "cold."</i>

26
00:02:18,884 --> 00:02:23,377
<i>It's rare for passion to spark.</i>

27
00:02:25,174 --> 00:02:27,413
<i>But...</i>

28
00:02:27,413 --> 00:02:29,133
- PD Shin.
- Yes?

29
00:02:29,133 --> 00:02:30,883
You can head out first.

30
00:02:30,883 --> 00:02:32,966
- Sorry?
- We're going to...

31
00:02:32,966 --> 00:02:36,179
look around and grab lunch.

32
00:02:37,202 --> 00:02:39,633
- Then I'll...
- No, it's fine.

33
00:02:39,633 --> 00:02:42,359
- No, I'll make the reservation.
- No.

34
00:02:43,333 --> 00:02:46,306
We'll take care of it.

35
00:02:47,931 --> 00:02:50,304
You can go.

36
00:02:51,208 --> 00:02:52,758
Okay.

37
00:02:52,758 --> 00:02:54,844
See you later.

38
00:02:57,229 --> 00:02:59,882
<i>I don't like that.</i>

39
00:03:10,049 --> 00:03:11,883
<i>No sense of boundaries.</i>

40
00:03:11,883 --> 00:03:15,234
<i>All that matters is how he feels.</i>

41
00:03:22,091 --> 00:03:23,383
Hello.

42
00:03:23,383 --> 00:03:26,376
I really don't like that.

43
00:03:30,258 --> 00:03:33,571
Whatever. Not my problem.

44
00:04:00,202 --> 00:04:01,542
Wait, is that a fire?

45
00:04:01,542 --> 00:04:02,917
What is that?

46
00:04:02,917 --> 00:04:05,657
I didn't light anything.

47
00:04:11,940 --> 00:04:14,359
It's warm.

48
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:18,706
They spent the whole day together
and he just got in.

49
00:04:18,706 --> 00:04:21,634
Is this thing actually happening?

50
00:04:21,634 --> 00:04:22,743
I'm telling you,

51
00:04:22,743 --> 00:04:26,216
he is absolutely giddy.

52
00:04:26,216 --> 00:04:28,473
Is that so?

53
00:04:32,924 --> 00:04:36,117
This is so annoying.

54
00:04:37,049 --> 00:04:41,424
<i>The only time someone
in low-power mode burns up</i>

55
00:04:41,424 --> 00:04:44,423
<i>isn't when they like someone,</i>

56
00:04:44,423 --> 00:04:47,091
<i>it's when they don't.</i>

57
00:04:47,091 --> 00:04:50,049
But honestly,
don't they seem like a pretty good match?

58
00:04:50,049 --> 00:04:51,466
Not really.

59
00:04:51,466 --> 00:04:53,625
What?

60
00:04:53,625 --> 00:04:55,158
I don't think they go together that well.

61
00:04:55,158 --> 00:04:57,306
Not a match? Why not? I think they'd be great.

62
00:04:57,306 --> 00:04:59,174
No,

63
00:04:59,174 --> 00:05:00,958
they're not a match.

64
00:05:00,958 --> 00:05:03,245
[Writer Kim Ju Ho]

65
00:05:04,458 --> 00:05:07,000
<i>What now?</i>

66
00:05:10,505 --> 00:05:11,533
Hello.

67
00:05:11,533 --> 00:05:13,216
<i>Hey, PD Shin.</i>

68
00:05:13,216 --> 00:05:15,926
<i>You left with Writer Kim, right?</i>

69
00:05:16,716 --> 00:05:18,754
<i>Yeah, so what?</i>

70
00:05:18,754 --> 00:05:21,102
Yes, since it's dark...

71
00:05:22,216 --> 00:05:25,133
<i>She's still up, right?</i>

72
00:05:25,133 --> 00:05:27,383
But she isn't picking up.

73
00:05:27,383 --> 00:05:32,508
Bring Writer Kim and come here.

74
00:05:32,508 --> 00:05:34,703
Sorry?

75
00:05:34,703 --> 00:05:36,730
What a boomer.

76
00:05:37,587 --> 00:05:39,915
I seriously hate him.

77
00:05:42,841 --> 00:05:45,174
She can't come.

78
00:05:45,174 --> 00:05:47,549
<i>What? How come?</i>

79
00:05:47,549 --> 00:05:51,383
She said she'd watch a movie, so we came.

80
00:05:51,383 --> 00:05:53,924
It just started, so two more hours.

81
00:05:53,924 --> 00:05:56,466
<i>- What?</i>
- Wait, hold on.

82
00:05:56,466 --> 00:05:57,958
That's a lie.

83
00:05:57,958 --> 00:05:59,008
<i>What movie?</i>

84
00:05:59,008 --> 00:06:00,995
So don't call her.

85
00:06:00,995 --> 00:06:03,716
She won't pick up.

86
00:06:03,716 --> 00:06:06,216
Wait, Soon Rok. You sure about this?

87
00:06:06,216 --> 00:06:07,789
Yes.

88
00:06:09,133 --> 00:06:11,593
Yes, understood.

89
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:18,583
You don't need to butt in like this.

90
00:06:18,583 --> 00:06:19,799
Who is that?

91
00:06:19,799 --> 00:06:21,966
I'm the only one awake.

92
00:06:21,966 --> 00:06:24,932
Who the hell is doing this?

93
00:06:33,051 --> 00:06:35,841
Emotion Cell, what are you doing up?

94
00:06:35,841 --> 00:06:37,258
I'm building a fire.

95
00:06:37,258 --> 00:06:40,084
What? Why?

96
00:06:41,750 --> 00:06:44,283
No, don't do anything pointless.

97
00:06:44,283 --> 00:06:46,885
I just hate that guy.

98
00:06:48,750 --> 00:06:50,633
Hey, let go!

99
00:06:50,633 --> 00:06:53,421
I said no!

100
00:06:53,421 --> 00:06:55,887
Hold it in!

101
00:07:05,841 --> 00:07:09,883
"Want to watch the movie together?"

102
00:07:10,581 --> 00:07:13,799
What is that?

103
00:07:13,799 --> 00:07:17,034
<i>You said solo's easier.</i>

104
00:07:18,217 --> 00:07:21,917
No, wait, Soon Rok.

105
00:07:21,917 --> 00:07:25,258
[Want to watch the movie together?]
[You said solo's easier]

106
00:07:25,258 --> 00:07:28,297
<i>Want to watch together?</i>

107
00:07:30,542 --> 00:07:33,167
<i>I'll head over now.</i>

108
00:07:34,116 --> 00:07:36,684
<i>I'll be there in ten.</i>

109
00:07:39,716 --> 00:07:42,606
<i>I'll grab the tickets.</i>

110
00:07:44,442 --> 00:07:47,258
This is so not like you, Soon Rok.

111
00:07:47,258 --> 00:07:50,133
Why are you butting in?

112
00:07:50,133 --> 00:07:52,966
She wants to see the movie too.

113
00:07:52,966 --> 00:07:55,959
She said she did.

114
00:08:00,044 --> 00:08:03,044
Oh, there it is.

115
00:08:15,674 --> 00:08:19,927
What? Did Writer Kim get here already?

116
00:08:22,549 --> 00:08:25,133
What is this?

117
00:08:25,133 --> 00:08:27,833
What the hell is this?

118
00:08:27,833 --> 00:08:30,417
This is bad.

119
00:08:49,466 --> 00:08:51,712
Writer Kim!

120
00:08:58,889 --> 00:09:02,508
What do you want to drink?

121
00:09:02,508 --> 00:09:05,074
Coffee? Coke?

122
00:09:08,191 --> 00:09:11,799
Since it's late, Coke sounds better, right?

123
00:09:11,799 --> 00:09:13,375
Hey, let's get one more Coke.

124
00:09:13,375 --> 00:09:14,510
Okay.

125
00:09:14,510 --> 00:09:17,050
One more Coke, please.

126
00:09:20,263 --> 00:09:21,625
I came too.

127
00:09:21,625 --> 00:09:23,786
Heard you were seeing a movie.

128
00:09:23,786 --> 00:09:26,633
I actually wanted to see it anyway,

129
00:09:26,633 --> 00:09:28,633
so I rushed over.

130
00:09:28,633 --> 00:09:31,673
Good thing it hasn't started yet.

131
00:09:32,383 --> 00:09:33,674
What?

132
00:09:33,674 --> 00:09:35,945
Wait, what is this?

133
00:09:35,945 --> 00:09:38,008
I think Writer Kim Ju Ho told him

134
00:09:38,008 --> 00:09:40,324
to text Yumi.

135
00:09:40,324 --> 00:09:41,758
No way.

136
00:09:41,758 --> 00:09:43,174
I think that's it.

137
00:09:43,174 --> 00:09:46,258
He figured Yumi wouldn't show up.

138
00:09:51,336 --> 00:09:54,095
What the...

139
00:09:54,095 --> 00:09:58,008
Are you guys kidding me?

140
00:10:03,383 --> 00:10:04,466
I see.

141
00:10:04,466 --> 00:10:06,133
Actually, we were just

142
00:10:06,133 --> 00:10:08,799
thinking about going for another round,

143
00:10:08,799 --> 00:10:10,424
but a movie sounds better.

144
00:10:10,424 --> 00:10:13,397
I'm into the arts too.

145
00:10:16,008 --> 00:10:17,841
I see.

146
00:10:17,841 --> 00:10:20,216
Hey, which theater is it?

147
00:10:20,216 --> 00:10:22,216
Is it that way?

148
00:10:22,216 --> 00:10:24,201
Yes.

149
00:10:24,201 --> 00:10:26,591
Writer Kim, this way.

150
00:10:26,591 --> 00:10:28,898
Let's go.

151
00:10:48,091 --> 00:10:49,979
Excuse me.

152
00:10:49,979 --> 00:10:52,216
Here.

153
00:10:52,216 --> 00:10:54,704
- Here.
- Thank you.

154
00:10:58,167 --> 00:11:00,875
Watching a movie in Busan feels kind of new.

155
00:11:00,875 --> 00:11:02,189
It brings back memories.

156
00:11:02,189 --> 00:11:03,203
Yeah.

157
00:11:04,841 --> 00:11:08,424
When I came to Busan for a baseball game,

158
00:11:08,424 --> 00:11:10,341
I did not want to go home,

159
00:11:10,341 --> 00:11:14,351
so I watched a movie and took the train after.

160
00:11:15,549 --> 00:11:17,242
I see.

161
00:11:45,832 --> 00:11:47,453
Oh my.

162
00:11:49,031 --> 00:11:51,508
It is funnier than I expected.

163
00:11:51,508 --> 00:11:54,008
This is good. I thought it would be serious.

164
00:11:54,008 --> 00:11:55,208
I will step out first.

165
00:11:55,208 --> 00:11:56,818
I need the restroom.

166
00:11:56,818 --> 00:11:59,046
Sure.

167
00:12:04,045 --> 00:12:05,216
PD Shin.

168
00:12:05,216 --> 00:12:06,883
Where should we go next?

169
00:12:06,883 --> 00:12:08,125
Sorry?

170
00:12:08,125 --> 00:12:09,174
"Next?"

171
00:12:09,174 --> 00:12:11,591
It feels too early to call it a night.

172
00:12:11,591 --> 00:12:14,674
I don't think she will want a bar,

173
00:12:14,674 --> 00:12:16,216
so maybe we grab some beers

174
00:12:16,216 --> 00:12:19,289
and take a walk by the beach?

175
00:12:24,038 --> 00:12:26,674
I told you not to butt in.

176
00:12:26,674 --> 00:12:28,133
What is this?

177
00:12:28,133 --> 00:12:31,633
This happened because you lit that fire.

178
00:12:31,633 --> 00:12:34,044
I didn't light it.

179
00:12:34,044 --> 00:12:35,549
It is your campfire.

180
00:12:35,549 --> 00:12:37,441
If not you, then who?

181
00:12:37,441 --> 00:12:38,799
I don't know.

182
00:12:38,799 --> 00:12:41,758
When I woke up, it was already burning.

183
00:12:41,758 --> 00:12:44,404
That makes no sense.

184
00:12:44,404 --> 00:12:45,896
Just go to sleep.

185
00:12:45,896 --> 00:12:48,796
I don't even have the energy to argue.

186
00:12:59,049 --> 00:13:01,383
<i>Yumi, let it go today.</i>

187
00:13:01,383 --> 00:13:03,669
<i>It's too late.</i>

188
00:13:12,716 --> 00:13:15,042
Oh, Writer Kim.

189
00:13:15,042 --> 00:13:16,799
Would you like a beer?

190
00:13:16,799 --> 00:13:19,116
We can get some fresh air by the beach.

191
00:13:19,116 --> 00:13:21,252
Writer Kim.

192
00:13:21,924 --> 00:13:24,966
Do you like me?

193
00:13:24,966 --> 00:13:26,466
- Sorry?
- I really hate guys

194
00:13:26,466 --> 00:13:28,883
who sneak up like this,

195
00:13:28,883 --> 00:13:31,633
playing it off like a joke.

196
00:13:31,633 --> 00:13:34,633
Maybe you think that works on women,

197
00:13:34,633 --> 00:13:36,674
but it doesn't work on me.

198
00:13:36,674 --> 00:13:38,667
You keep using PD Shin as an excuse,

199
00:13:38,667 --> 00:13:41,508
then sending him away halfway through.

200
00:13:41,508 --> 00:13:44,309
Isn't that a bit outdated?

201
00:13:46,174 --> 00:13:47,680
Oh, no.

202
00:13:47,680 --> 00:13:49,271
Is that how you saw it?

203
00:13:49,271 --> 00:13:50,299
That's not...

204
00:13:50,299 --> 00:13:52,633
I asked if you like me.

205
00:13:52,633 --> 00:13:53,799
Do you have feelings for me?

206
00:13:53,799 --> 00:13:56,726
Do you want something with me?

207
00:13:57,758 --> 00:14:00,133
Why not just be honest?

208
00:14:00,133 --> 00:14:02,383
You always talk about "our generation."

209
00:14:02,383 --> 00:14:04,091
Yeah, we're old enough.

210
00:14:04,091 --> 00:14:06,341
We know what we're doing, right?

211
00:14:06,341 --> 00:14:09,258
Yeah. Right.

212
00:14:09,258 --> 00:14:11,008
So you like me?

213
00:14:11,008 --> 00:14:14,034
And you want to see where this goes?

214
00:14:17,049 --> 00:14:18,549
Yes.

215
00:14:18,549 --> 00:14:21,266
I'd like to see where things go with you.

216
00:14:21,266 --> 00:14:23,966
I see.

217
00:14:23,966 --> 00:14:26,091
But

218
00:14:26,091 --> 00:14:28,008
I'm not interested.

219
00:14:28,008 --> 00:14:29,049
- Sorry?
- I don't want

220
00:14:29,049 --> 00:14:31,008
to see you outside of work.

221
00:14:31,008 --> 00:14:35,549
So please don't do this again.

222
00:14:35,549 --> 00:14:38,133
And PD Shin,

223
00:14:38,133 --> 00:14:40,549
is this part of your job?

224
00:14:40,549 --> 00:14:43,508
Do you usually handle things like this
for your writers?

225
00:14:43,508 --> 00:14:47,174
This isn't work. It's overstepping.

226
00:14:47,174 --> 00:14:50,549
Doing this doesn't make you a better PD.

227
00:14:50,549 --> 00:14:53,520
It really doesn't.

228
00:14:56,466 --> 00:14:58,674
Thanks for the movie.

229
00:14:58,674 --> 00:14:59,924
Since it was on you,

230
00:14:59,924 --> 00:15:03,133
I'll get you both coffee tomorrow.

231
00:15:03,133 --> 00:15:06,286
I should go. See you tomorrow.

232
00:15:18,633 --> 00:15:21,326
Did I just get rejected?

233
00:15:24,799 --> 00:15:28,508
She just shut me down like that?

234
00:15:28,508 --> 00:15:29,633
That was...

235
00:15:29,633 --> 00:15:32,339
She totally slammed the door on me.

236
00:15:37,635 --> 00:15:40,008
That was unbelievable, seriously.

237
00:15:40,008 --> 00:15:42,174
Good.

238
00:15:42,174 --> 00:15:45,133
I thought he was decent,
but how can he play with people like that?

239
00:15:45,133 --> 00:15:46,341
That was perfect.

240
00:15:46,341 --> 00:15:48,424
You had to say it.

241
00:15:49,202 --> 00:15:50,883
Beats me.

242
00:15:50,883 --> 00:15:52,508
I'm done.

243
00:15:52,508 --> 00:15:54,008
Just forget it.

244
00:15:54,008 --> 00:15:57,121
Yeah. Let's just drop it.

245
00:16:24,924 --> 00:16:27,144
- Thanks.
- Bye.

246
00:16:32,274 --> 00:16:34,167
Excuse me, where are the umbrellas?

247
00:16:34,167 --> 00:16:37,154
We just sold the last one.

248
00:17:08,258 --> 00:17:11,216
Emotion Cell, there you are.

249
00:17:11,216 --> 00:17:12,924
What are you doing?

250
00:17:12,924 --> 00:17:15,591
You were all fired up earlier...

251
00:17:15,591 --> 00:17:17,258
I feel sad.

252
00:17:17,258 --> 00:17:21,674
I actually felt something
for Soon Rok for once.

253
00:17:21,674 --> 00:17:25,474
I was really excited. It's been a while.

254
00:17:26,166 --> 00:17:28,499
Don't cry.

255
00:18:06,370 --> 00:18:08,133
Writer Kim.

256
00:18:08,133 --> 00:18:10,597
There you are.

257
00:18:11,591 --> 00:18:14,637
I saw it pouring and came after you.

258
00:18:15,883 --> 00:18:17,549
You don't even have an umbrella.

259
00:18:17,549 --> 00:18:19,030
Why follow me?

260
00:18:19,030 --> 00:18:21,466
I was going to buy you one.

261
00:18:21,466 --> 00:18:25,269
They're sold out.

262
00:18:25,269 --> 00:18:28,066
So I'm just standing here too.

263
00:18:30,341 --> 00:18:32,301
Oh, okay.

264
00:18:50,299 --> 00:18:53,872
There should be another store nearby.

265
00:19:07,966 --> 00:19:10,266
About earlier...

266
00:19:11,652 --> 00:19:13,529
I'm sorry.

267
00:19:15,924 --> 00:19:19,383
I wasn't in a great mood.

268
00:19:19,383 --> 00:19:21,742
I don't think he meant any harm, but...

269
00:19:30,299 --> 00:19:32,049
No.

270
00:19:32,049 --> 00:19:34,425
You were cool.

271
00:19:36,341 --> 00:19:37,867
What?

272
00:19:40,315 --> 00:19:42,312
You were so cool.

273
00:20:02,179 --> 00:20:05,049
There's a convenience store over there.

274
00:20:05,049 --> 00:20:07,258
Wait here for a second.

275
00:20:22,875 --> 00:20:26,555
[Episode 14: Soon Rok's Principles]

276
00:20:43,383 --> 00:20:45,549
Soon Rok,

277
00:20:45,549 --> 00:20:48,341
why did you say that just now?

278
00:20:48,341 --> 00:20:51,049
Calling Writer Kim cool...

279
00:20:51,049 --> 00:20:54,258
Are you sure that was okay?

280
00:20:54,258 --> 00:20:58,263
Feels like a rule violation.

281
00:21:07,715 --> 00:21:09,091
Do you have umbrellas here?

282
00:21:09,091 --> 00:21:10,799
- Over there.
- Thanks.

283
00:21:10,799 --> 00:21:13,619
Wait, this won't work.

284
00:21:14,457 --> 00:21:17,404
Emergency power, on!

285
00:21:23,410 --> 00:21:24,966
What?

286
00:21:25,883 --> 00:21:27,924
What is that?

287
00:21:28,766 --> 00:21:32,542
Why are you waking us up?

288
00:21:32,542 --> 00:21:34,883
We can't just ignore this.

289
00:21:34,883 --> 00:21:38,276
Bring me Kim Yumi's chart. Now.

290
00:21:40,232 --> 00:21:41,258
Here.

291
00:21:41,258 --> 00:21:43,091
Name, Kim Yumi.

292
00:21:43,091 --> 00:21:44,764
Occupation, writer.

293
00:21:44,764 --> 00:21:47,591
Relationship, work.

294
00:21:47,591 --> 00:21:49,591
Priority, high.

295
00:21:49,591 --> 00:21:52,010
Closeness, low.

296
00:21:52,010 --> 00:21:53,799
Affinity, average.

297
00:21:53,799 --> 00:21:55,091
See?

298
00:21:55,091 --> 00:21:57,799
There's nothing special here. Just work.

299
00:21:57,799 --> 00:22:00,924
She's just one of the writers under contract.

300
00:22:00,924 --> 00:22:03,341
He's not even assigned to her right now.

301
00:22:03,341 --> 00:22:06,466
So was his actions today appropriate?

302
00:22:06,466 --> 00:22:08,258
Did he follow the rules?

303
00:22:08,258 --> 00:22:10,633
Soon Rok's Principle one.

304
00:22:10,633 --> 00:22:11,758
<i>Writer Kim,</i>

305
00:22:11,758 --> 00:22:14,341
<i>want to watch the movie together?</i>

306
00:22:14,341 --> 00:22:16,258
He doesn't go to the movies alone

307
00:22:16,258 --> 00:22:19,591
with someone he doesn't have feelings for.

308
00:22:19,591 --> 00:22:21,174
Soon Rok's Principle two.

309
00:22:21,174 --> 00:22:23,101
<i>You were so cool.</i>

310
00:22:23,101 --> 00:22:27,591
He doesn't evaluate a writer
on anything but their work.

311
00:22:27,591 --> 00:22:30,908
He broke two core principles.

312
00:22:30,908 --> 00:22:32,091
All because

313
00:22:32,091 --> 00:22:34,744
Emotion Cell lost control.

314
00:22:34,744 --> 00:22:37,345
Emotion Cell? Seriously?

315
00:22:37,345 --> 00:22:39,341
I told you, I didn't start the fire.

316
00:22:39,341 --> 00:22:41,716
Either way, the rules were broken.

317
00:22:41,716 --> 00:22:45,327
She's just a work contact.

318
00:22:51,466 --> 00:22:52,716
Is there only one umbrella?

319
00:22:52,716 --> 00:22:55,133
Yes, that's the last one.

320
00:23:08,466 --> 00:23:10,926
Let's wrap this up.

321
00:23:11,883 --> 00:23:15,042
Is he close enough
to watch a movie alone with Writer?

322
00:23:15,042 --> 00:23:16,091
No.

323
00:23:16,091 --> 00:23:18,758
Is he close enough to call her cool?

324
00:23:18,758 --> 00:23:19,799
No.

325
00:23:19,799 --> 00:23:22,591
Is he close enough to share an umbrella?

326
00:23:22,591 --> 00:23:24,481
No.

327
00:23:33,716 --> 00:23:35,299
Conclusion.

328
00:23:35,299 --> 00:23:38,569
We don't cross the line anymore.

329
00:23:42,133 --> 00:23:44,878
How far did he go?

330
00:23:55,923 --> 00:23:58,733
That looks like Soon Rok.

331
00:24:02,483 --> 00:24:04,917
It's Soon Rok!

332
00:24:12,296 --> 00:24:14,406
Writer Kim.

333
00:24:15,299 --> 00:24:16,674
Where did you go?

334
00:24:16,674 --> 00:24:19,954
They only had one umbrella there too.

335
00:24:22,441 --> 00:24:23,591
Take this.

336
00:24:23,591 --> 00:24:24,966
What about you?

337
00:24:24,966 --> 00:24:26,883
I'm already soaked.

338
00:24:26,883 --> 00:24:29,091
I should get back to Writer Kim Ju Ho.

339
00:24:29,091 --> 00:24:31,003
But...

340
00:24:34,299 --> 00:24:37,411
I'll get going.

341
00:24:39,424 --> 00:24:41,371
Wait...

342
00:24:49,771 --> 00:24:51,799
Alright, that settles it.

343
00:24:51,799 --> 00:24:53,591
Emergency over.

344
00:24:53,591 --> 00:24:56,184
Wait, look behind him!

345
00:25:18,341 --> 00:25:21,719
I can't just take this by myself.

346
00:25:21,719 --> 00:25:24,758
We can go to the hotel and borrow an umbrella.

347
00:25:24,758 --> 00:25:26,716
Come on.

348
00:25:26,716 --> 00:25:28,549
What now?

349
00:25:28,549 --> 00:25:30,341
What's he going to do?

350
00:25:30,341 --> 00:25:32,758
What if she asks to share?

351
00:25:32,758 --> 00:25:35,216
In that case...

352
00:25:35,216 --> 00:25:38,549
That's not in his rulebook.

353
00:25:46,258 --> 00:25:47,466
What is this?

354
00:25:47,466 --> 00:25:49,008
Why is he walking so far away?

355
00:25:49,008 --> 00:25:51,299
Is he seriously keeping his distance?

356
00:25:51,299 --> 00:25:52,841
Come closer.

357
00:25:52,841 --> 00:25:54,140
You're getting soaked.

358
00:25:54,140 --> 00:25:57,854
I'm already soaked, so it's fine.

359
00:26:17,475 --> 00:26:18,508
Oh my.

360
00:26:18,508 --> 00:26:19,799
What is this now?

361
00:26:19,799 --> 00:26:22,219
This is like a drama.

362
00:26:22,219 --> 00:26:24,549
I'll hold the umbrella.

363
00:26:24,549 --> 00:26:25,674
Okay.

364
00:26:25,674 --> 00:26:27,882
Let's go.

365
00:26:29,030 --> 00:26:31,083
This way.

366
00:26:31,083 --> 00:26:32,990
Okay.

367
00:26:54,674 --> 00:26:56,924
Do you think

368
00:26:56,924 --> 00:26:59,549
he's really upset?

369
00:26:59,549 --> 00:27:02,379
You don't have to worry about it.

370
00:27:03,299 --> 00:27:06,674
Still, it's hard not to worry at all.

371
00:27:06,674 --> 00:27:08,174
You said what you needed to say.

372
00:27:08,174 --> 00:27:11,127
You really don't have to worry.

373
00:27:24,841 --> 00:27:26,383
A Maltese!

374
00:27:26,383 --> 00:27:27,758
Isn't that a Maltese?

375
00:27:27,758 --> 00:27:29,049
This one?

376
00:27:29,049 --> 00:27:31,966
Yeah, it is.

377
00:27:31,966 --> 00:27:33,924
I thought you didn't like Maltese.

378
00:27:33,924 --> 00:27:36,174
Why do you have a picture of one?

379
00:27:36,174 --> 00:27:38,049
That's my dog.

380
00:27:38,049 --> 00:27:39,841
Kongsoon.

381
00:27:39,841 --> 00:27:43,554
My parents take care of her now,
so I don't see her much.

382
00:27:44,867 --> 00:27:46,174
But I don't think

383
00:27:46,174 --> 00:27:50,936
I ever said I don't like Maltese.

384
00:27:50,936 --> 00:27:53,216
No, I'm pretty sure you did...

385
00:27:53,216 --> 00:27:55,508
You said it that time.

386
00:27:55,508 --> 00:27:56,841
<i>Yeah.</i>

387
00:27:56,841 --> 00:27:58,883
<i>By any chance...</i>

388
00:27:58,883 --> 00:28:01,799
<i>do you not like dogs?</i>

389
00:28:01,799 --> 00:28:04,633
You asked if I was scared or had allergies,

390
00:28:04,633 --> 00:28:06,591
and I said not really.

391
00:28:06,591 --> 00:28:08,074
<i>No, not really.</i>

392
00:28:08,074 --> 00:28:11,133
<i>Oh, that's a relief.</i>

393
00:28:11,133 --> 00:28:14,744
<i>Then could you pet her?</i>

394
00:28:16,113 --> 00:28:19,091
<i>You want me to?</i>

395
00:28:19,091 --> 00:28:21,258
But you didn't even want to pet her...

396
00:28:21,258 --> 00:28:22,674
I thought she might bite.

397
00:28:22,674 --> 00:28:23,841
My Kongsoon...

398
00:28:23,841 --> 00:28:27,104
she bites strangers sometimes.

399
00:28:27,924 --> 00:28:29,549
<i>But Maltese</i>

400
00:28:29,549 --> 00:28:30,841
<i>aren't that smart.</i>

401
00:28:30,841 --> 00:28:32,508
Oh, right.

402
00:28:32,508 --> 00:28:34,049
You said Maltese aren't very smart.

403
00:28:34,049 --> 00:28:36,466
Kongsoon isn't that smart either.

404
00:28:36,466 --> 00:28:38,966
She even gets lost sometimes.

405
00:28:38,966 --> 00:28:40,466
But...

406
00:28:40,466 --> 00:28:42,001
<i>Maltese...</i>

407
00:28:42,001 --> 00:28:43,424
<i>Don't they eat poop?</i>

408
00:28:43,424 --> 00:28:45,049
Oh, and...

409
00:28:45,049 --> 00:28:47,091
You said Maltese eat poop too.

410
00:28:47,091 --> 00:28:50,255
Kongsoon eats her own sometimes.

411
00:28:52,216 --> 00:28:54,466
But she's still really cute, right?

412
00:28:54,466 --> 00:28:56,799
I got her when I was in high school,

413
00:28:56,799 --> 00:28:59,558
and she's already thirteen.

414
00:29:01,979 --> 00:29:04,466
Usually when people see a dog,

415
00:29:04,466 --> 00:29:07,799
they talk about their own too, huh?

416
00:29:07,799 --> 00:29:09,133
When I'm at work,

417
00:29:09,133 --> 00:29:12,559
I don't really talk about personal things.

418
00:29:14,133 --> 00:29:17,000
That's impressive.

419
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:18,049
What?

420
00:29:18,049 --> 00:29:20,446
It's a compliment.

421
00:29:22,091 --> 00:29:24,715
Doesn't sound like one.

422
00:29:25,299 --> 00:29:27,845
It is.

423
00:29:31,799 --> 00:29:34,232
Let's go.

424
00:29:45,091 --> 00:29:47,837
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

425
00:29:53,091 --> 00:29:56,049
You can keep that umbrella.

426
00:29:56,049 --> 00:29:58,411
It might rain again tomorrow.

427
00:29:59,091 --> 00:30:01,341
Okay.

428
00:30:01,341 --> 00:30:04,034
Get some rest.

429
00:30:17,508 --> 00:30:21,008
Now I get what kind of person Soon Rok is.

430
00:30:21,008 --> 00:30:22,966
He...

431
00:30:22,966 --> 00:30:25,158
only says what's true.

432
00:30:25,158 --> 00:30:27,008
If it's tricky, he just says nothing.

433
00:30:27,008 --> 00:30:28,799
If he says it, he means it.

434
00:30:28,799 --> 00:30:30,091
Right.

435
00:30:30,091 --> 00:30:31,466
So...

436
00:30:31,466 --> 00:30:33,508
when he said Yumi was cool,

437
00:30:33,508 --> 00:30:36,572
he meant it.

438
00:30:38,549 --> 00:30:40,574
Shin Soon Rok.

439
00:30:40,574 --> 00:30:43,892
He is turning this whole place upside down.

440
00:30:43,892 --> 00:30:46,592
He's trouble. Real trouble.

441
00:31:24,216 --> 00:31:26,049
Writer...

442
00:31:26,049 --> 00:31:28,091
Did you wait long?

443
00:31:28,091 --> 00:31:32,411
They were all sold out,
so I had to borrow one from the hotel.

444
00:31:34,424 --> 00:31:37,258
Did Writer Kim get back okay?

445
00:31:37,258 --> 00:31:40,049
- Yeah.
- Okay...

446
00:31:40,049 --> 00:31:42,883
That was seriously embarrassing earlier,

447
00:31:42,883 --> 00:31:44,049
but

448
00:31:44,049 --> 00:31:46,258
something just hit me.

449
00:31:46,258 --> 00:31:48,258
What?

450
00:31:48,258 --> 00:31:49,799
Inspiration.

451
00:31:49,799 --> 00:31:53,466
We were stuck on Ji Hoon
and Su Jeong's storyline,

452
00:31:53,466 --> 00:31:55,299
but after getting shut down like that,

453
00:31:55,299 --> 00:31:58,672
ideas just started pouring in.

454
00:31:58,672 --> 00:32:02,098
So I was writing it all down just now.

455
00:32:02,098 --> 00:32:04,018
- That's good.
- Yeah.

456
00:32:04,018 --> 00:32:06,341
At least I got something out of it.

457
00:32:06,341 --> 00:32:09,174
It wasn't a total waste.

458
00:32:09,174 --> 00:32:12,693
- Let's go.
- Yeah, let's go.

459
00:32:14,133 --> 00:32:16,549
But hey,

460
00:32:16,549 --> 00:32:19,855
something's been bugging me.

461
00:32:22,258 --> 00:32:25,424
What you said earlier...

462
00:32:25,424 --> 00:32:27,533
She hadn't even arrived yet, so why did you say

463
00:32:27,533 --> 00:32:31,526
she'd be watching the movie
and not to call her?

464
00:32:34,133 --> 00:32:38,739
That part stuck with me.

465
00:32:40,899 --> 00:32:41,924
Darn it.

466
00:32:41,924 --> 00:32:44,377
Another emergency!

467
00:32:45,399 --> 00:32:46,966
Name, Kim Ju Ho.

468
00:32:46,966 --> 00:32:48,633
Relationship, assigned writer.

469
00:32:48,633 --> 00:32:50,383
Priority, very high.

470
00:32:50,383 --> 00:32:52,091
Closeness, average.

471
00:32:52,091 --> 00:32:53,792
Affinity, very low.

472
00:32:53,792 --> 00:32:54,841
Focus.

473
00:32:54,841 --> 00:32:57,424
Priority is very high here.

474
00:32:57,424 --> 00:32:59,591
Hey, focus.

475
00:32:59,591 --> 00:33:02,249
Is he someone he can be honest with?

476
00:33:02,249 --> 00:33:03,424
No.

477
00:33:03,424 --> 00:33:06,895
Would being honest help the work?

478
00:33:09,561 --> 00:33:11,008
No.

479
00:33:11,008 --> 00:33:13,758
- Agreed.
- Exactly.

480
00:33:13,758 --> 00:33:15,841
Soon Rok's Principle three.

481
00:33:15,841 --> 00:33:20,008
If he can't be honest, he stays silent.

482
00:33:20,008 --> 00:33:23,534
I thought about why you said that,

483
00:33:24,341 --> 00:33:26,508
and it probably means
you don't like how I do things.

484
00:33:26,508 --> 00:33:28,716
Right?

485
00:33:28,716 --> 00:33:30,674
Like, "You pathetic writer."

486
00:33:30,674 --> 00:33:34,049
"Stop messing around and keep your mouth shut."

487
00:33:34,049 --> 00:33:36,269
Something like that, huh?

488
00:33:42,258 --> 00:33:44,508
So basically, you don't like me.

489
00:33:44,508 --> 00:33:46,799
Then

490
00:33:46,799 --> 00:33:49,341
if we think differently,

491
00:33:49,341 --> 00:33:50,966
do I have to adjust?

492
00:33:50,966 --> 00:33:54,214
Do I have to adjust to you?

493
00:33:58,091 --> 00:34:01,091
- No.
- Then what?

494
00:34:01,091 --> 00:34:04,997
Don't say anything, Soon Rok.

495
00:34:18,234 --> 00:34:20,220
Writer Kim.

496
00:34:25,258 --> 00:34:27,716
- Did you sleep well?
- Yeah, did you?

497
00:34:27,716 --> 00:34:29,258
Yeah.

498
00:34:29,258 --> 00:34:32,091
I heard you went all the way to a fourth round.

499
00:34:32,091 --> 00:34:33,341
You're up early.

500
00:34:33,341 --> 00:34:35,749
I passed out and then got up.

501
00:34:36,716 --> 00:34:38,466
You look pretty refreshed.

502
00:34:38,466 --> 00:34:41,341
The sauna here is great.

503
00:34:41,341 --> 00:34:42,633
And for breakfast,

504
00:34:42,633 --> 00:34:44,091
I highly recommend the pho.

505
00:34:44,091 --> 00:34:46,387
It clears you right up.

506
00:34:46,387 --> 00:34:50,299
That's why you look so fresh.

507
00:34:50,299 --> 00:34:51,799
Would you like some coffee?

508
00:34:51,799 --> 00:34:53,500
Yes, please.

509
00:34:53,500 --> 00:34:55,958
A hot latte.

510
00:34:57,387 --> 00:35:00,118
I heard you watched a movie last night.

511
00:35:00,118 --> 00:35:02,633
Yeah.

512
00:35:02,633 --> 00:35:07,066
I'd been wanting to see it,
and it was the last showing.

513
00:35:07,066 --> 00:35:08,924
How did you know?

514
00:35:08,924 --> 00:35:11,258
You got in pretty late last night.

515
00:35:11,258 --> 00:35:12,783
I talked to Ju Ho.

516
00:35:12,783 --> 00:35:14,883
He already got on the train.

517
00:35:14,883 --> 00:35:17,299
Oh, he went back to Seoul?

518
00:35:17,299 --> 00:35:18,758
Yeah.

519
00:35:18,758 --> 00:35:21,299
No way it's because of Yumi.

520
00:35:21,299 --> 00:35:23,299
I see.

521
00:35:23,299 --> 00:35:24,633
But why so suddenly...

522
00:35:24,633 --> 00:35:26,042
He had an interview.

523
00:35:26,042 --> 00:35:27,674
It was already scheduled.

524
00:35:27,674 --> 00:35:30,397
Oh, okay.

525
00:35:30,397 --> 00:35:32,133
Good, that's a relief.

526
00:35:32,133 --> 00:35:34,216
So Soon Rok went too?

527
00:35:34,216 --> 00:35:35,383
Already?

528
00:35:35,383 --> 00:35:38,924
Then PD Shin went with him?

529
00:35:38,924 --> 00:35:40,758
No, he's in his room.

530
00:35:40,758 --> 00:35:43,341
He got soaked in the rain
and caught a bad cold.

531
00:35:43,341 --> 00:35:45,508
He's completely down.

532
00:35:45,508 --> 00:35:47,047
Oh no.

533
00:35:48,174 --> 00:35:50,875
By the way,

534
00:35:50,875 --> 00:35:53,372
- Yeah?
- last night...

535
00:35:57,299 --> 00:35:59,799
Oh, sorry, I should get going.

536
00:35:59,799 --> 00:36:01,424
Make sure you eat.

537
00:36:01,424 --> 00:36:02,758
Hello, sir.

538
00:36:02,758 --> 00:36:04,341
Yeah.

539
00:36:04,341 --> 00:36:06,216
What was that? That felt off.

540
00:36:06,216 --> 00:36:08,591
Yeah, something's off.

541
00:36:08,591 --> 00:36:12,664
Writer Kim Ju Ho left early this morning...

542
00:36:38,173 --> 00:36:40,042
Yes?

543
00:36:40,042 --> 00:36:41,091
Hello,

544
00:36:41,091 --> 00:36:44,244
it's Kim Yumi.

545
00:36:50,008 --> 00:36:51,966
Writer Kim?

546
00:36:51,966 --> 00:36:54,459
Are you okay? I heard you're sick.

547
00:36:55,424 --> 00:36:57,799
Yeah, just a bit of a cold.

548
00:36:57,799 --> 00:37:00,107
It's nothing serious.

549
00:37:02,133 --> 00:37:04,341
From the rain last night, right?

550
00:37:04,341 --> 00:37:06,049
Gosh...

551
00:37:06,049 --> 00:37:08,758
I'm fine. I took medicine.

552
00:37:10,216 --> 00:37:12,008
But

553
00:37:12,008 --> 00:37:14,466
did something happen?

554
00:37:14,466 --> 00:37:15,492
What?

555
00:37:15,492 --> 00:37:18,828
I heard Writer Kim Ju Ho left early.

556
00:37:19,591 --> 00:37:20,741
He had an interview.

557
00:37:20,741 --> 00:37:23,299
Didn't you go with him?

558
00:37:23,299 --> 00:37:24,982
Me?

559
00:37:27,591 --> 00:37:31,167
I didn't need to go anymore.

560
00:37:31,167 --> 00:37:32,216
What?

561
00:37:32,216 --> 00:37:33,841
I got cut.

562
00:37:33,841 --> 00:37:35,940
Yesterday.

563
00:37:51,750 --> 00:37:54,367
[Episode 15: Love X-Ray]

564
00:37:55,376 --> 00:37:58,383
You got cut from his team?

565
00:37:58,383 --> 00:38:00,000
Yesterday?

566
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:01,640
Why all of a sudden?

567
00:38:02,383 --> 00:38:03,633
I guess

568
00:38:03,633 --> 00:38:06,174
he really was upset yesterday.

569
00:38:06,174 --> 00:38:08,258
It's because of me, right?

570
00:38:08,258 --> 00:38:11,208
- No.
- I think it is.

571
00:38:11,208 --> 00:38:12,258
No.

572
00:38:12,258 --> 00:38:15,128
- If not...
- Writer Kim.

573
00:38:16,012 --> 00:38:18,758
We're heading to Gamcheon Village today, right?

574
00:38:18,758 --> 00:38:21,049
That team leaves in ten minutes,

575
00:38:21,049 --> 00:38:23,125
- so please get ready.
- Okay, got it.

576
00:38:23,125 --> 00:38:26,591
PD Shin was supposed to lead, but he's sick.

577
00:38:26,591 --> 00:38:28,633
I'm sorry.

578
00:38:28,633 --> 00:38:31,216
PD Yoo will take that group.

579
00:38:31,216 --> 00:38:32,966
So please come to the lobby right away.

580
00:38:32,966 --> 00:38:34,393
Okay.

581
00:38:38,354 --> 00:38:39,508
- Then...
- Hello, it's me.

582
00:38:39,508 --> 00:38:41,466
Have a good trip.

583
00:38:41,466 --> 00:38:44,594
Thanks, get some rest.

584
00:38:49,583 --> 00:38:52,958
What is with that writer?

585
00:38:55,716 --> 00:38:57,258
Unbelievable, Kim Ju Ho.

586
00:38:57,258 --> 00:38:59,006
His pride got hurt?

587
00:38:59,006 --> 00:39:01,216
He couldn't say a word to Yumi,

588
00:39:01,216 --> 00:39:03,208
so why take it out on Soon Rok?

589
00:39:03,208 --> 00:39:06,500
We should just call him and say something.

590
00:39:08,883 --> 00:39:12,129
We can't just let this slide.

591
00:39:13,600 --> 00:39:16,270
Someone has to say something.

592
00:39:17,758 --> 00:39:19,716
This isn't right.

593
00:39:36,111 --> 00:39:37,633
Writer Kim, over here.

594
00:39:37,633 --> 00:39:39,258
- Hurry up.
- Just a second.

595
00:39:39,258 --> 00:39:40,466
Come on.

596
00:39:40,466 --> 00:39:42,091
Everyone's already on.

597
00:39:42,091 --> 00:39:44,508
- Come on, over here.
- Hello.

598
00:39:45,193 --> 00:39:48,222
- Take good care of them.
- Yeah.

599
00:39:48,222 --> 00:39:50,679
Have a good trip.

600
00:40:07,457 --> 00:40:09,134
Writer Kim.

601
00:40:09,134 --> 00:40:10,883
Did you sleep well?

602
00:40:10,883 --> 00:40:13,076
Yeah.

603
00:40:15,780 --> 00:40:18,005
By the way,

604
00:40:18,005 --> 00:40:21,546
did something happen with Writer Ju Ho?

605
00:40:21,546 --> 00:40:23,383
Why?

606
00:40:23,383 --> 00:40:25,674
He got seriously upset

607
00:40:25,674 --> 00:40:28,883
and went back to Seoul.

608
00:40:28,883 --> 00:40:30,513
He even cut PD Shin.

609
00:40:30,513 --> 00:40:31,549
What?

610
00:40:31,549 --> 00:40:35,341
That rumor spread fast.

611
00:40:35,341 --> 00:40:38,216
Where did you hear that?

612
00:40:38,216 --> 00:40:40,341
Who do you think?

613
00:40:40,341 --> 00:40:42,447
From him.

614
00:40:43,641 --> 00:40:44,966
He spent all night

615
00:40:44,966 --> 00:40:46,741
talking to Writer Yoon

616
00:40:46,741 --> 00:40:49,674
about PD Shin.

617
00:40:49,674 --> 00:40:52,091
He was upset at him.

618
00:40:52,091 --> 00:40:54,799
What did he say again...

619
00:40:54,799 --> 00:40:58,424
That he was arrogant or something.

620
00:40:58,424 --> 00:40:59,883
Ju Ho is

621
00:40:59,883 --> 00:41:02,250
always like that.

622
00:41:02,250 --> 00:41:03,341
That's why his nickname is

623
00:41:03,341 --> 00:41:06,404
Mr. Sensitive.

624
00:41:37,133 --> 00:41:39,174
Everyone, please move this way.

625
00:41:39,174 --> 00:41:40,258
- Okay.
- Yeah.

626
00:41:40,258 --> 00:41:42,841
Oh my God!

627
00:41:42,841 --> 00:41:45,367
This feels so freeing!

628
00:41:56,341 --> 00:41:58,216
- Excuse me, PD Yoo.
- Yes?

629
00:41:58,216 --> 00:42:01,034
Go ahead. I just need to make a quick call.

630
00:42:01,034 --> 00:42:02,466
Okay, just follow this path.

631
00:42:02,466 --> 00:42:05,077
- We'll go slowly.
- Okay.

632
00:42:11,773 --> 00:42:12,799
Hello?

633
00:42:12,799 --> 00:42:14,417
<i>- Hello.</i>
- Yeah.

634
00:42:14,417 --> 00:42:16,549
<i>- Do you have a moment?</i>
- Of course.

635
00:42:16,549 --> 00:42:18,008
Are you enjoying the trip?

636
00:42:18,008 --> 00:42:19,049
Yes.

637
00:42:19,049 --> 00:42:23,008
About what you were saying earlier...

638
00:42:23,008 --> 00:42:24,674
What I was saying?

639
00:42:24,674 --> 00:42:25,841
Yes, you asked

640
00:42:25,841 --> 00:42:30,091
if something happened last night.

641
00:42:30,091 --> 00:42:32,031
Oh, right.

642
00:42:35,174 --> 00:42:38,049
I heard the three of you went to a movie,

643
00:42:38,049 --> 00:42:41,174
so I thought you might know something.

644
00:42:41,174 --> 00:42:43,440
He really likes Soon Rok,

645
00:42:43,440 --> 00:42:45,591
but suddenly he said
he couldn't work with him anymore.

646
00:42:45,591 --> 00:42:48,909
<i>Something about feeling disrespected.</i>

647
00:42:48,909 --> 00:42:50,258
This morning?

648
00:42:50,258 --> 00:42:51,991
Yes, he called out of nowhere.

649
00:42:51,991 --> 00:42:54,008
It caught me off guard too.

650
00:42:54,008 --> 00:42:56,850
And PD Shin won't say a word.

651
00:42:56,850 --> 00:43:00,667
<i>I don't know
if something happened after drinking...</i>

652
00:43:00,667 --> 00:43:03,867
Actually, something did happen.

653
00:43:05,383 --> 00:43:06,883
What happened?

654
00:43:06,883 --> 00:43:08,841
But honestly,

655
00:43:08,841 --> 00:43:11,924
it's just so childish.

656
00:43:11,924 --> 00:43:14,799
I'd rather not say it myself.

657
00:43:14,799 --> 00:43:17,992
It might be better
to hear it from him directly.

658
00:43:19,379 --> 00:43:21,549
Childish?

659
00:43:21,549 --> 00:43:24,169
Yes, really childish.

660
00:43:28,906 --> 00:43:29,924
Well,

661
00:43:29,924 --> 00:43:31,674
he can be childish.

662
00:43:31,674 --> 00:43:34,594
But that's kind of his charm too.

663
00:43:34,594 --> 00:43:36,758
That's not charming to everyone.

664
00:43:36,758 --> 00:43:38,674
Even on a first meeting?

665
00:43:38,674 --> 00:43:40,324
Oh, well...

666
00:43:40,324 --> 00:43:42,591
No, that's not okay for a first meeting.

667
00:43:42,591 --> 00:43:44,184
Anyway,

668
00:43:44,184 --> 00:43:46,966
I feel really bad for PD Shin.

669
00:43:46,966 --> 00:43:48,883
This doesn't feel right.

670
00:43:48,883 --> 00:43:51,763
I was hoping you could help resolve it.

671
00:43:53,591 --> 00:43:55,833
Then...

672
00:43:56,883 --> 00:43:58,216
what if

673
00:43:58,216 --> 00:44:02,424
PD Shin joins your team again?

674
00:44:02,424 --> 00:44:03,966
- What?
<i>- I mean...</i>

675
00:44:03,966 --> 00:44:06,799
You said you felt sorry for Soon Rok,

676
00:44:06,799 --> 00:44:09,633
so I just thought I'd suggest it.

677
00:44:09,633 --> 00:44:11,072
Say yes.

678
00:44:11,072 --> 00:44:13,079
Say yes!

679
00:44:15,509 --> 00:44:17,258
That would be fine.

680
00:44:17,258 --> 00:44:19,226
I'm okay with it.

681
00:44:19,226 --> 00:44:20,841
Really?

682
00:44:20,841 --> 00:44:22,466
Yes.

683
00:44:22,466 --> 00:44:25,549
It was just a scheduling issue before, right?

684
00:44:25,549 --> 00:44:29,466
I actually liked PD Shin's feedback.

685
00:44:29,466 --> 00:44:31,633
Great, great.

686
00:44:31,633 --> 00:44:32,883
But

687
00:44:32,883 --> 00:44:35,316
his opinion matters too.

688
00:44:35,316 --> 00:44:37,125
Do we really need to hear it?

689
00:44:37,125 --> 00:44:39,799
He caused trouble,
so he should just go along with it.

690
00:44:39,799 --> 00:44:41,605
That's a bit...

691
00:44:41,605 --> 00:44:43,466
I'll talk to him

692
00:44:43,466 --> 00:44:44,841
when I get back.

693
00:44:44,841 --> 00:44:46,549
Alright, thank you.

694
00:44:46,549 --> 00:44:48,581
Yeah.

695
00:44:52,511 --> 00:44:54,357
Oh...

696
00:44:55,216 --> 00:44:57,869
Is this really happening?

697
00:45:00,190 --> 00:45:03,024
Is this a good thing?

698
00:45:03,024 --> 00:45:04,716
It is!

699
00:45:15,549 --> 00:45:16,799
Guys,

700
00:45:16,799 --> 00:45:19,339
Soon Rok is coming back.

701
00:45:23,133 --> 00:45:25,883
Let's have meetings every day when he's back.

702
00:45:25,883 --> 00:45:29,401
Then we'll see him every day!

703
00:45:30,622 --> 00:45:31,650
Are you crazy?

704
00:45:31,650 --> 00:45:32,883
Writers don't just sit in meetings.

705
00:45:32,883 --> 00:45:34,708
They're supposed to write!

706
00:45:34,708 --> 00:45:36,841
That's not my concern.

707
00:45:36,841 --> 00:45:40,491
I'm just really happy right now.

708
00:45:42,813 --> 00:45:44,750
Well, yeah.

709
00:45:44,750 --> 00:45:46,734
I guess it worked out.

710
00:45:47,758 --> 00:45:49,966
Maybe you should tell Soon Rok.

711
00:45:49,966 --> 00:45:52,258
It'd be weird if he hears it from the editor.

712
00:45:52,258 --> 00:45:54,084
Yeah.

713
00:46:05,174 --> 00:46:07,383
Why isn't he picking up?

714
00:46:07,383 --> 00:46:09,424
<i>- The call cannot be completed.</i>
- Writer Kim!

715
00:46:09,424 --> 00:46:10,841
Everyone's waiting.

716
00:46:10,841 --> 00:46:13,442
Okay, coming.

717
00:46:13,442 --> 00:46:15,207
Amazing.

718
00:46:15,207 --> 00:46:16,966
- We should take pictures here.
- Sounds good.

719
00:46:16,966 --> 00:46:18,724
- Everyone, gather up.
- Okay.

720
00:46:18,724 --> 00:46:20,341
Writer Kim, over here.

721
00:46:20,341 --> 00:46:22,633
- Stand in the best spot.
- No, I'm fine.

722
00:46:22,633 --> 00:46:24,716
- Come on over.
- Thank you.

723
00:46:24,716 --> 00:46:27,158
Let's do heart poses today.

724
00:46:27,158 --> 00:46:29,508
- Sounds good.
- One, two, three.

725
00:46:29,508 --> 00:46:30,591
Heart.

726
00:46:30,591 --> 00:46:32,883
That's really pretty.

727
00:46:32,883 --> 00:46:35,008
The colors are so nice.

728
00:46:35,008 --> 00:46:36,424
This view is incredible.

729
00:46:36,424 --> 00:46:39,008
Every house is a different color.

730
00:46:39,008 --> 00:46:41,661
One, two, three.

731
00:46:54,716 --> 00:46:57,210
Why isn't he calling?

732
00:47:15,752 --> 00:47:18,672
Busan is stunning!

733
00:47:19,508 --> 00:47:21,841
Would you two like to head
to the restaurant on your own?

734
00:47:21,841 --> 00:47:23,299
I'm a bit hot,

735
00:47:23,299 --> 00:47:26,383
so I'll grab an iced Americano
and cool off first.

736
00:47:26,383 --> 00:47:28,758
I've been sweating so much.

737
00:47:28,758 --> 00:47:31,091
Is it okay if I skip it?

738
00:47:31,091 --> 00:47:34,083
I ate too much this morning,
so I'm not really hungry.

739
00:47:34,083 --> 00:47:35,147
Of course.

740
00:47:35,147 --> 00:47:37,674
We have dinner plans later anyway.

741
00:47:37,674 --> 00:47:39,133
Then we'll head over first.

742
00:47:39,133 --> 00:47:41,008
- Okay.
- Yeah.

743
00:47:41,008 --> 00:47:43,214
Want to grab a drink?

744
00:48:08,829 --> 00:48:12,283
Am I waking him up for nothing?

745
00:48:15,607 --> 00:48:17,667
<i>PD Shin, how are you feeling...</i>

746
00:48:17,667 --> 00:48:19,841
Excuse me,

747
00:48:19,841 --> 00:48:23,809
are you with the guest in room 410?

748
00:48:23,809 --> 00:48:25,133
Yes.

749
00:48:25,133 --> 00:48:27,466
Is the young man okay?

750
00:48:27,466 --> 00:48:29,185
Sorry?

751
00:48:29,185 --> 00:48:30,716
What do you mean?

752
00:48:30,716 --> 00:48:33,424
He was very sick earlier
and went to the hospital.

753
00:48:33,424 --> 00:48:35,250
I was wondering if he's okay now.

754
00:48:35,250 --> 00:48:36,299
What?

755
00:48:36,299 --> 00:48:40,652
I recommended a nearby clinic.

756
00:48:42,015 --> 00:48:44,453
Where is it?

757
00:48:50,845 --> 00:48:52,958
All set.

758
00:48:54,442 --> 00:48:56,442
Welcome.

759
00:48:56,442 --> 00:48:59,466
Has someone named Shin Soon Rok come in?

760
00:48:59,466 --> 00:49:00,549
Shin Soon Rok?

761
00:49:00,549 --> 00:49:02,258
Yes, could you check?

762
00:49:02,258 --> 00:49:04,326
Sure.

763
00:49:12,049 --> 00:49:14,216
He had a high fever, so he's on an IV.

764
00:49:14,216 --> 00:49:16,409
I see.

765
00:50:00,822 --> 00:50:04,169
I just wanted to check if your fever went down.

766
00:50:04,791 --> 00:50:08,141
The nurse said it was really high.

767
00:50:10,091 --> 00:50:12,844
It seems a lot better now, thankfully.

768
00:50:13,966 --> 00:50:16,633
How did you find this place?

769
00:50:16,633 --> 00:50:19,133
The hotel staff told me.

770
00:50:19,133 --> 00:50:21,674
I was worried when I couldn't reach you.

771
00:50:21,674 --> 00:50:23,758
Weren't you at Gamcheon Village earlier?

772
00:50:23,758 --> 00:50:26,133
I already went.

773
00:50:29,049 --> 00:50:31,367
One moment please.

774
00:50:32,716 --> 00:50:34,133
- I'll remove the IV now.
- Okay.

775
00:50:34,133 --> 00:50:36,031
I'll wait outside.

776
00:50:45,781 --> 00:50:46,833
All done.

777
00:50:46,833 --> 00:50:48,167
Thank you.

778
00:51:29,133 --> 00:51:31,461
I knew this would happen.

779
00:51:36,141 --> 00:51:37,174
What are you doing?

780
00:51:37,174 --> 00:51:39,742
It's flaring up again.

781
00:51:40,809 --> 00:51:42,133
It's not me.

782
00:51:42,133 --> 00:51:44,453
I was asleep.

783
00:51:45,924 --> 00:51:48,633
I told you, it wasn't me.

784
00:51:48,633 --> 00:51:51,133
Right, it wasn't you.

785
00:51:51,133 --> 00:51:52,716
It was Writer Kim.

786
00:51:52,716 --> 00:51:53,799
What?

787
00:51:53,799 --> 00:51:57,133
She's the one who asked to watch the movie.

788
00:51:57,133 --> 00:51:59,299
She's the one who wanted to share the umbrella.

789
00:51:59,299 --> 00:52:01,758
She's the one who touched his forehead.

790
00:52:01,758 --> 00:52:04,054
See? It wasn't me.

791
00:52:04,054 --> 00:52:06,607
We need to see Love Cell.

792
00:52:14,135 --> 00:52:16,062
Love Cell.

793
00:52:17,683 --> 00:52:19,639
Soon Rok's Love Cell

794
00:52:19,639 --> 00:52:22,841
is a renowned surgeon.

795
00:52:22,841 --> 00:52:25,398
Is this a photo of Writer Kim?

796
00:52:25,398 --> 00:52:26,424
Yeah.

797
00:52:26,424 --> 00:52:29,466
You're great at reading X-rays, right?

798
00:52:29,466 --> 00:52:32,752
Take a look at her feelings.

799
00:52:36,108 --> 00:52:37,383
What do you see?

800
00:52:37,383 --> 00:52:40,258
See this here?

801
00:52:40,258 --> 00:52:42,336
It looks like a heart.

802
00:52:43,758 --> 00:52:45,258
What is that?

803
00:52:45,258 --> 00:52:47,133
Wait, is it a tumor?

804
00:52:47,133 --> 00:52:48,797
No.

805
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:53,086
It's a love X-ray!

806
00:52:56,633 --> 00:53:00,508
This is a compound of interest and curiosity.

807
00:53:00,508 --> 00:53:02,924
Interest and curiosity?

808
00:53:02,924 --> 00:53:04,424
It's still in the early stage.

809
00:53:04,424 --> 00:53:06,758
But if it keeps growing,

810
00:53:06,758 --> 00:53:08,170
it turns into love.

811
00:53:08,170 --> 00:53:10,990
Then what should Soon Rok do?

812
00:53:19,924 --> 00:53:21,799
If he accepts her feelings,

813
00:53:21,799 --> 00:53:24,049
that's when a relationship begins.

814
00:53:24,049 --> 00:53:28,312
But he doesn't date within work relationships.

815
00:53:30,542 --> 00:53:32,519
[Ongyeol Internal Medicine Clinic]

816
00:53:37,883 --> 00:53:39,976
Wait long?

817
00:53:40,796 --> 00:53:42,091
Are you okay?

818
00:53:42,091 --> 00:53:43,633
Yeah, I'm fine.

819
00:53:43,633 --> 00:53:45,457
I feel much better.

820
00:53:45,457 --> 00:53:48,314
I picked up the meds.

821
00:53:48,314 --> 00:53:51,525
Oh, thanks.

822
00:53:51,525 --> 00:53:53,133
Let's grab lunch.

823
00:53:53,133 --> 00:53:56,174
There's a porridge place nearby
with good reviews.

824
00:53:56,174 --> 00:53:57,897
Well, I'm not really hungry.

825
00:53:57,897 --> 00:54:00,133
You need to eat to take your meds.

826
00:54:00,133 --> 00:54:02,823
And I'm hungry too.

827
00:54:04,424 --> 00:54:07,379
I'll treat. Let's go.

828
00:54:15,939 --> 00:54:17,591
They say this place is good.

829
00:54:17,591 --> 00:54:20,966
Apparently not all porridge is the same.

830
00:54:20,966 --> 00:54:23,466
Looks legit.

831
00:54:23,466 --> 00:54:26,924
You've been through a lot since yesterday
because of me.

832
00:54:26,924 --> 00:54:28,656
Not at all.

833
00:54:29,883 --> 00:54:32,799
What will you be working on
once you're back in Seoul?

834
00:54:32,799 --> 00:54:35,383
Since you're off Writer Ju Ho's team...

835
00:54:35,383 --> 00:54:36,508
I'm not sure.

836
00:54:36,508 --> 00:54:38,633
I'll hand things over first.

837
00:54:38,633 --> 00:54:41,604
Probably stay in-office for a while.

838
00:54:41,604 --> 00:54:43,924
Stuff like overseas rights

839
00:54:43,924 --> 00:54:46,930
and tedious paperwork.

840
00:54:49,049 --> 00:54:50,549
Come back

841
00:54:50,549 --> 00:54:52,883
on my project.

842
00:54:52,883 --> 00:54:55,091
You only stepped off because of scheduling.

843
00:54:55,091 --> 00:54:56,750
Now that it's sorted,

844
00:54:56,750 --> 00:55:00,417
it makes sense for you to rejoin, right?

845
00:55:02,258 --> 00:55:04,466
That's not really my call.

846
00:55:04,466 --> 00:55:07,216
Then I'll talk to the editor

847
00:55:07,216 --> 00:55:09,986
and decide from there.

848
00:55:12,216 --> 00:55:15,586
Alright, we'll talk it over.

849
00:55:17,001 --> 00:55:19,674
Nice. Cool and professional.

850
00:55:19,674 --> 00:55:22,680
You didn't show a thing.

851
00:55:26,383 --> 00:55:29,216
Join her team again?

852
00:55:29,216 --> 00:55:30,799
What should you do?

853
00:55:30,799 --> 00:55:32,508
It'd be good for him.

854
00:55:32,508 --> 00:55:35,341
He likes her writing.

855
00:55:35,341 --> 00:55:37,049
And she's a good person.

856
00:55:37,049 --> 00:55:38,549
Not like Kim Ju Ho.

857
00:55:38,549 --> 00:55:41,102
Then what about this?

858
00:55:42,232 --> 00:55:44,883
Accept it or not?

859
00:55:44,883 --> 00:55:48,133
He doesn't date at work.

860
00:55:48,133 --> 00:55:49,841
He doesn't want to mess things up.

861
00:55:49,841 --> 00:55:52,341
And he hates complications.

862
00:55:52,341 --> 00:55:55,016
Then let's cut it off now.

863
00:55:56,334 --> 00:55:59,500
Before it gets bigger.

864
00:56:02,230 --> 00:56:05,324
[Surgery in progress]

865
00:56:16,466 --> 00:56:19,083
Starting the procedure.

866
00:56:19,083 --> 00:56:20,126
Scalpel!

867
00:56:20,126 --> 00:56:21,517
Scalpel.

868
00:56:23,299 --> 00:56:25,424
It might hurt her,

869
00:56:25,424 --> 00:56:27,999
but this is the best way.

870
00:56:30,799 --> 00:56:32,299
Enjoy your meal.

871
00:56:32,299 --> 00:56:33,466
Thank you.

872
00:56:33,466 --> 00:56:35,848
That's a lot.

873
00:56:35,848 --> 00:56:38,261
I've got it.

874
00:56:44,049 --> 00:56:46,966
- Hello?
<i>- Where are you?</i>

875
00:56:46,966 --> 00:56:49,633
Just left the hospital.

876
00:56:49,633 --> 00:56:52,883
Having lunch with Writer Kim.

877
00:56:52,883 --> 00:56:55,674
She came early too.

878
00:56:55,674 --> 00:56:57,633
About 30 minutes?

879
00:57:00,841 --> 00:57:03,133
Yeah, I'll eat and head back.

880
00:57:03,133 --> 00:57:04,966
Okay.

881
00:57:04,966 --> 00:57:06,424
Oh, by the way.

882
00:57:06,424 --> 00:57:08,716
About what you mentioned.

883
00:57:08,716 --> 00:57:11,049
That plan.

884
00:57:11,049 --> 00:57:15,089
- Can you set it up?
<i>- Oh, you're going through with it?</i>

885
00:57:21,008 --> 00:57:24,133
I just... changed my mind.

886
00:57:24,133 --> 00:57:26,591
I'll try to fit it into my schedule.

887
00:57:26,591 --> 00:57:28,637
Okay.

888
00:57:30,459 --> 00:57:32,008
That was PD Jang.

889
00:57:32,008 --> 00:57:34,699
Their team just got back to the hotel.

890
00:57:35,549 --> 00:57:39,320
What kind of plan was that?
Her voice got so excited.

891
00:57:39,320 --> 00:57:42,040
I could hear it.

892
00:57:42,924 --> 00:57:45,337
A blind date.

893
00:57:45,337 --> 00:57:47,383
I kept turning them down because I was busy,

894
00:57:47,383 --> 00:57:50,963
but now I've got time, so I figured why not.

895
00:57:57,008 --> 00:57:58,033
I didn't know

896
00:57:58,033 --> 00:58:02,341
you went on blind dates.

897
00:58:02,341 --> 00:58:04,549
I'm not exactly against them.

898
00:58:04,549 --> 00:58:07,235
I see.

899
00:58:10,466 --> 00:58:12,292
Hope it goes well.

900
00:58:14,841 --> 00:58:17,073
Do you know anyone?

901
00:58:18,091 --> 00:58:19,133
Who?

902
00:58:19,133 --> 00:58:22,073
Someone who could set me up.

903
00:58:22,831 --> 00:58:25,049
The one on the receiving end knows.

904
00:58:25,049 --> 00:58:28,802
He's drawing a line.

905
00:58:34,174 --> 00:58:36,383
So it hurts,

906
00:58:36,383 --> 00:58:38,568
but it can't be helped.

907
00:58:45,008 --> 00:58:47,781
I'll look into it.

908
00:58:48,966 --> 00:58:50,482
Okay.

909
00:58:55,591 --> 00:58:57,372
This is good.

910
00:59:17,216 --> 00:59:18,799
Thanks for today.

911
00:59:18,799 --> 00:59:21,466
Get some rest,
and make sure you take your meds.

912
00:59:21,466 --> 00:59:22,974
Okay.

913
00:59:47,216 --> 00:59:51,351
Good. Looks like the surgery was a success.

914
01:00:08,299 --> 01:00:10,799
This workshop was a mess.

915
01:00:10,799 --> 01:00:12,383
Broke all the rules.

916
01:00:12,383 --> 01:00:14,758
No boundaries between work and personal.

917
01:00:14,758 --> 01:00:18,365
Let's not let that happen again.

918
01:00:42,232 --> 01:00:43,966
- Good work.
- Yeah.

919
01:00:43,966 --> 01:00:46,664
Let's get some rest.

920
01:00:53,875 --> 01:00:55,133
What's this?

921
01:00:55,133 --> 01:00:57,974
There's another photo.

922
01:00:57,974 --> 01:00:59,443
Wait.

923
01:01:00,133 --> 01:01:03,076
This isn't the one we removed.

924
01:01:03,076 --> 01:01:04,838
What is this?

925
01:01:06,014 --> 01:01:08,193
How come...

926
01:01:21,174 --> 01:01:25,034
<i>I just thought of someone. A junior I know.</i>

927
01:01:26,258 --> 01:01:28,133
<i>I think she'd be a great match for you.</i>

928
01:01:28,133 --> 01:01:30,491
<i>Want to meet her?</i>

929
01:01:46,766 --> 01:01:50,249
That's not Writer Kim's photo, is it?

930
01:01:50,249 --> 01:01:52,135
[Shin Soon Rok]

931
01:01:53,049 --> 01:01:55,867
This is his photo!

932
01:02:29,716 --> 01:02:31,091
<i>Are you still at your studio?</i>

933
01:02:31,091 --> 01:02:33,856
<i>If things aren't going well,
feel free to reach out anytime.</i>

934
01:02:33,856 --> 01:02:36,674
<i>I'm terrible at games.</i>

935
01:02:36,674 --> 01:02:38,216
<i>I've got plans.</i>

936
01:02:38,216 --> 01:02:39,924
<i>- Good luck.
- Today's Sunday...</i>

937
01:02:39,924 --> 01:02:42,008
<i>It's his blind date day.</i>

938
01:02:42,008 --> 01:02:43,799
<i>How did it go?</i>

939
01:02:43,799 --> 01:02:45,799
<i>She even called to wish him luck...</i>

940
01:02:45,799 --> 01:02:47,591
<i>Was drawing that line really necessary?</i>

941
01:02:47,591 --> 01:02:50,049
<i>Did you reach out to Jenny?</i>

942
01:02:50,049 --> 01:02:51,841
<i>Do I really have to?</i>

943
01:02:51,841 --> 01:02:54,643
<i>Isn't that PD Shin over there?</i>
